text: FINALLY!!! FINALLY!!! FINALLY!!! I have been waiting (severely impatiently) for this movie for ten years! I cannot put into words how much I LOVE this book! It changed my life for the better by teaching me a new way to navigate life's challenges, when I was struggling through my darkest year. I am alive because of this book. I have been recommending it to friends ever since, but they don't read or they only read escapist genre fiction. I don't mean to bash sci-fi or fantasy (some of my other favorite books are sci-fi and fantasy), but it bothers me when anyone reads one or two types of book to the complete exclusion of works that don't fit their narrow scope because they miss out on so many great things that they would probably enjoy if only they were willing to give something different a chance. So I've been waiting for this movie so I can FINALLY share one of my favorite stories with them. Plus, I love the vibrance, thunder, and POWER of racecars, so that's a happy bonus.

text: So, my wife and kids convinced me to see this film with them. I recall seeing the trailer and was like, OK, a kids flick, silly cliche film etc. All I can say is, that I was wrong. This film drew every emotion you could imagine for us. I had no clue what the film was about or even was aware of the book that this film apparently followed closely. How this film started and methods used to deliver the story at times felt long, though necessary as it took a while to bond to the characters. At the end, you can tell that this was the intent, like you were getting to know these people as if they were your friends. The acting was OK, though the story, the narrative, the messages were so critical to life. This might be worth your watching and if you do, bring a box of tissue.
